    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-19T06:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-19T06:35:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6789: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-19T15:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 19, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 20—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>253. My 230, October 24, noon.<note n="33" xml:id="d559fn33">Not printed.</note>
                    Similar source<note n="34" xml:id="d559fn34">Not identified.</note> now
                    states:</p>
                <p>(1) Soviets have promised Berlin not to interfere with German and Italian
                    projects in the Balkans in return for Turkish Armenia and, <pb facs="0649"
                        n="637" xml:id="pg_637"/> if the Soviets should consider it vital, portions
                    of northern Iran. See also Legation’s 248, November 14, 3 p.m.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
